data.body:
while verifying https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/issues/4027:

if a stackframe has no source, it does not make sense to show the source line:
![2016-03-23 12-20-35](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1898161/13983836/8a97dfec-f0f2-11e5-9c40-278ea602b009.png)

- VSCode Version: 0.10.12-alpha
- OS Version: Windows10

Steps to Reproduce:
1.  Launch app and open any folder which contains .ts file.
2. Add below code in the file and compare it with Visual studio.

Actual: 'require' is not highlighted.
Expected: As 'require' is provided by CommonJS compliant system so it should be highlighted with blue color.

 import http = require('http');
var port = process.env.port || 1337
http.createServer(function (req, res) {
    res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' });
    res.end('Hello World\n');
}).listen(port);

